Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7. Chop the @Potatoes{450%g} into 2cm wide wedges (no need to peel).

Pop the wedges onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{some}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-35%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, grate the @Mature Cheddar Cheese{30%g}. Trim the @Baby Gem Lettuce{1%unit}, separate the leaves, then tear into bite-sized pieces.

When the wedges have 10-12 mins remaining, heat a drizzle of @oil{some} in large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, fry the @Unconventional Plant-Based Burgers{2} until browned, ~{3-4%minutes} on each side.

When the burgers are cooked, remove the pan from the heat. Carefully place the cheese on top of the burgers. Cover with a #lid{} (or #foil{}), then set aside, off the heat, to allow the cheese to melt, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Just before everything's ready, halve the @Burger Buns{2}. Transfer the buns to a medium baking tray and pop into the oven until warmed through, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Meanwhile, in a medium #bowl{}, add the @Burger Sauce{45%g} and toss the baby gem until coated.

When everything's ready, spread the @Mayonnaise{1%tbsp} over the bun bases and @BBQ Sauce{32%g} over the lids.

Top the bases with your cheeseburgers and some of the dressed baby gem, then sandwich shut with the bun lids.

Serve your burgers with the wedges and remaining baby gem alongside. Enjoy!